    <string name="help_title">Help</string>
    <string name="help_about">About</string>
    <string name="help_about_content">Tellraw Command Generator helps Minecraft players create tellraw commands.

Supports Java and Bedrock selector conversion, and text formatting.</string>
    <string name="help_selector_input">Selectors</string>
    <string name="help_selector_content">Selectors pick command targets:

• @a - All players
• @p - Nearest player
• @r - Random player
• @e - All entities
• @s - Command executor

Use filters like:
• @a[gamemode=survival] - All survival players
• @e[type=cow] - All cows
• @p[distance=..10] - Nearest player in 10 blocks</string>
    <string name="help_text_formatting">Text Colors</string>
    <string name="help_text_formatting_content">Use Minecraft color and format codes:

Colors:
• §0 - Black    §1 - Dark Blue   §2 - Dark Green
• §3 - Dark Aqua §4 - Dark Red    §5 - Dark Purple
• §6 - Gold     §7 - Gray        §8 - Dark Gray
• §9 - Blue     §a - Green       §b - Aqua
• §c - Red      §d - Light Purple §e - Yellow
• §f - White

Formats:
• §l - Bold     §m - Strike      §n - Underline
• §o - Italic   §k - Random      §r - Reset</string>
    <string name="help_version_differences">Version Differences</string>
    <string name="help_version_differences_content">Java and Bedrock use different selectors:

• Java: distance, Bedrock: r/rm
• Java: gamemode, Bedrock: m
• Java: nbt, Bedrock: hasitem

Text formats:
• §m§n codes work differently
• Some colors have special meanings in Bedrock</string>
    <string name="help_usage_tips">How to Use</string>
    <string name="help_usage_tips_content">1. Enter selector and message
2. App detects selector type
3. Generate Java and Bedrock commands
4. Copy or share commands

For §m§n codes:
• Font style: Java keeps format, Bedrock uses colors
• Color style: Both use colors</string>
    <string name="help_conversion_warning">Selector conversion is not perfect. Check manually.</string>
    
